No private ranch in Laikipia county offered scholarships to needy students this year, following a spate of attacks by migrant herders that is driving them out of business, leaders have said.Nominated MP Sarah Lekorere and Mukogodo East MCA Paul Leshuel spoke in Laikipia North yesterday while issuing cheques from the Rattansi Education Trust to orphans and other needy students.There have been spates of attacks by migrant herders.They have driven thousands of their livestock into private ranches in Laikipia in search of pasture and water as the drought in their counties persists. The national government ordered their eviction, but some leaders were against it.The attacks on ranches are made worse by the drought that has also hit Laikipia.